[ctns_make id='prZeroProductRuleS1']

    [ctns_problem_height]
        360
    [/ctns_problem_height]

    [ctns_problem_width]
        600
    [/ctns_problem_width]

    [ctns_front]
Zero Product Rule
    [/ctns_front]

    [ctns_back]
For all real numbers $$x,y \in \mathbb{R},$$<br/>
if $$ x \cdot y = 0$$, then either $$x = 0$$ or $$y = 0.$$
    [/ctns_back]

    [ctns_backspeak]
For all real numbers X and Y, -- if the product of X times Y equals zero, --
then either x equals zero -- or y equals zero.
    [/ctns_backspeak]

[/ctns_make]
